<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,778,1816]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,938,964]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Wing membrane with three brownish stripes; R 
<number box="[894,902,954,968]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[911,918,954,968]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="3.0">3</number>
reaching C very close to R 
<number box="[1243,1251,954,968]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="1.0">1</number>
; R 
<number box="[1286,1294,954,968]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="4.0">4</number>
with strong sinuosity; first flagellomere conical, shorter than pedicel; gonostylus strongly truncated distally, with a clump of setae; ejaculatory apodeme long, exceeding base of terminalia; gonocoxal apodeme short.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,778,1816]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,269,1061,1087]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Male.</emphasis>
Body length, 8.0– 
<quantity box="[488,582,1061,1087]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.2" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" unit="mm" value="8.2">8.2 mm</quantity>
. Wing length, 5.0– 
<quantity box="[806,900,1061,1087]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
. General color dark brown. Eyes dark brown, facets homogenous, ocellar tubercle dark brown, ocelli grayish. Gena and clypeus brownish gray; clypeus bare (
<figureCitation box="[221,344,1141,1167]" captionStart="FIGURES 93 – 97" captionStartId="30.[151,269,1914,1938]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,514,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[183,1404,514,1890]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 93 – 97. Chrysopilus fascipennis sp. n., male: 93 — Thorax, 94 — Maxillary palpus, 95 — Wing, 96 — Head, 97 — Antenna." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177252/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Figure 
<number box="[311,344,1141,1167]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="96.0">96</number>
</figureCitation>
). Antenna dark brown; scape bare, half the length of pedicel; pedicel almost cubic; first flagellomere conical, shorter than pedicel (
<figureCitation box="[651,770,1181,1207]" captionStart="FIGURES 93 – 97" captionStartId="30.[151,269,1914,1938]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,514,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[183,1404,514,1890]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 93 – 97. Chrysopilus fascipennis sp. n., male: 93 — Thorax, 94 — Maxillary palpus, 95 — Wing, 96 — Head, 97 — Antenna." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177252/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Figure 
<number box="[737,770,1181,1207]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="97.0">97</number>
</figureCitation>
). Maxillary palpus long and slender (
<figureCitation box="[1206,1325,1181,1207]" captionStart="FIGURES 93 – 97" captionStartId="30.[151,269,1914,1938]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,514,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[183,1404,514,1890]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 93 – 97. Chrysopilus fascipennis sp. n., male: 93 — Thorax, 94 — Maxillary palpus, 95 — Wing, 96 — Head, 97 — Antenna." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177252/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Figure 
<number box="[1292,1325,1181,1207]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="94.0">94</number>
</figureCitation>
); proboscis and labella dark brown. Occiput gray, with silvery iridescent setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,778,1816]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[298,416,1261,1287]" captionStart="FIGURES 93 – 97" captionStartId="30.[151,269,1914,1938]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,514,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[183,1404,514,1890]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 93 – 97. Chrysopilus fascipennis sp. n., male: 93 — Thorax, 94 — Maxillary palpus, 95 — Wing, 96 — Head, 97 — Antenna." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177252/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Figure 
<number box="[386,416,1261,1287]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="93.0">93</number>
</figureCitation>
) dark brown, with dark and golden setae. Halter bare, stem brown, tip yellow. Coxae and femora dark brown, with dark setae; tibiae brownish yellow. Wing membrane with three transverse brownish stripes (
<figureCitation box="[366,487,1341,1367]" captionStart="FIGURES 93 – 97" captionStartId="30.[151,269,1914,1938]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,514,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[183,1404,514,1890]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 93 – 97. Chrysopilus fascipennis sp. n., male: 93 — Thorax, 94 — Maxillary palpus, 95 — Wing, 96 — Head, 97 — Antenna." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177252/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Figure 
<number box="[454,487,1341,1367]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="95.0">95</number>
</figureCitation>
); pterostigma indistinguishable amid stripes; R 
<number box="[1056,1064,1357,1371]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[1074,1081,1357,1371]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="3.0">3</number>
reaching C very close to R 
<number box="[1420,1428,1357,1371]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="1.0">1</number>
, without distal sinuosity; proximal portion of R 
<number box="[713,721,1400,1414]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="4.0">4</number>
with strong concavity, without short appendage; R 
<number box="[1338,1346,1400,1414]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="4.0">4</number>
curved distally toward anterior margin; CuA 
<number box="[585,593,1443,1457]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="2.0">2</number>
and A 
<number box="[671,679,1443,1457]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="1.0">1</number>
fusing far from margin; crossvein m-m far from origin of M 
<number box="[1389,1397,1443,1457]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="2.0">2</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,778,1816]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Abdomen brown, yellow stripes on first three segments. Tergite of first abdominal segment with silvery setae forming an iridescent band. Gonocoxite and gonostylus brown; gonocoxite wider than long; gonostylus strongly truncated distally, with a clump of setae; aedeagus long; ejaculatory apodeme exceeding base of terminalia; gonocoxal apodeme short; lateral ejaculatory process slender, parallel to ejaculatory apodeme (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 98 – 99" captionStartId="31.[151,269,828,852]" captionTargetBox="[173,1411,197,804]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[173,1413,194,804]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 98 – 99. Chrysopilus fascipennis sp. n., male: 98 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 99 — Terminalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177253/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Figure 
<number box="[151,184,1630,1656]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="98.0">98</number>
</figureCitation>
); meso-anterior incision of tergite IX short (
<figureCitation box="[701,819,1630,1656]" captionStart="FIGURES 98 – 99" captionStartId="31.[151,269,828,852]" captionTargetBox="[173,1411,197,804]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[173,1413,194,804]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 98 – 99. Chrysopilus fascipennis sp. n., male: 98 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 99 — Terminalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177253/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Figure 
<number box="[786,819,1630,1656]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="99.0">99</number>
</figureCitation>
); cercus brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,778,1816]" box="[197,1132,1670,1696]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,295,1670,1696]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Female.</emphasis>
For general description and terminalia characters, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Pimentel" box="[935,1128,1670,1696]" pageId="29" pageNumber="33" refString="Pimentel, T. (1975) Contribuicao ao conhecimento de Chrysopilus fascipennis Bromley, 1931. Boletim do Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi, 78, 1 - 5." type="journal article" year="1975">
Pimentel (
<number box="[1056,1120,1670,1696]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="1975.0">1975</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,778,1816]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,357,1710,1736]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[368,652,1710,1735]" class="Insecta" family="Rhagionidae" genus="Chrysopilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fascipennis">
<emphasis box="[368,652,1710,1735]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Chrysopilus fascipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[893,965,1710,1736]" name="Brazil" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1028,1207,1710,1736]" name="Guyana" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">British Guiana</collectingCountry>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[1277,1380,1710,1736]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">holotype</typeStatus>
was formerly considered to be collected in Fonteboa, State of Amazonas, but it was a misinterpretation made by 
<bibRefCitation author="Curran" box="[151,320,1790,1816]" pageId="29" pageNumber="32" refString="Curran, C. H. (1931) New species of Chrysopilus from the Neotropical Region (Rhagionidae, Diptera). American Museum Novitates, 462, 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="1931">
Curran (
<number box="[248,311,1790,1816]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="1931.0">1931</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, since the 
<typeStatus box="[443,494,1790,1816]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">type</typeStatus>
label brings clearly Kartabo, in the 
<collectingCountry box="[914,1089,1790,1816]" name="Guyana" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">British Guiana</collectingCountry>
, as the type-locality.
</paragraph>
